comment._content: Background information to the swimmer's competition in this July 1908 newspaper article - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/12695230 .Evidently Etta Mackay beat Beatrice Kerr in Blackpool. And I think Maggie Scott was British.

comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] 'An easy victory'! Kerr apparently also challenged Kellerman to several races while they were both in the UK, however Kellerman declined on each occasion.
